# Gnosis addon — per-install runtime data (never committed).
#
# Everything under data/ is generated by the addon at runtime: saved run
# reports (character names + party info), per-machine config (API tokens),
# debug logs, in-progress snapshots. None of this should land in a public
# repo. The .note placeholder is what Windower expects to exist so the
# addon can write into the directory.

data/*
!data/.note

# Per-user credentials. Old name was sortiestats_*; styx_* is the modern
# convention; incessantvoid_* is the legacy fallback the addon still reads.
# All three carry the user's API token and MUST stay local.
sortiestats_config.json
styx_config.json
incessantvoid_config.json

# Live IPC + tracker state files (machine-local, not user-portable).
tracker_status.json
tracker_live.json
tracker_control.json
tracker_prefs.json

# Webhook URL — user-personal Discord. Forks must paste their own.
# Default in Gnosis.lua is a placeholder; runtime override goes to data/.
data/discord_webhook.txt
